         <abstract>
            <p>Let $F$ be an algebraic number field and denote by $N(a)$ the absolute norm and by $\overline a$ the maximum of the absolute values of the conjugates of the element $a$ of $F$. Define $c_F$ to be the best possible constant with the property: For every $a \in F$ there exists a unit $u$ of $F$ such that $\overline{ua} \leqslant c_FN(a)^{1/\lbrack F:\mathbf{Q} \rbrack}$. An algorithm for the computation of $c_F$ is described and some examples are given.</p>
          </abstract>
